## Physics & Neuroengineering Track: 18-Month Hands-On Program

### Overview

This track transforms theoretical physics knowledge into **professional neuroengineering capabilities** through 8 integrated phases. Each phase combines theory, hardware prototyping, and measurable outcomes‚Äîprogressing from basic circuits to clinical-grade brain-computer interfaces.

---

### Phase 1: Foundational Electronics (January ‚Äì March 2026 | Weeks 1‚Äì6)

**Weekly Time Commitment:** 6‚Äì8 hours

| Topic | Project | Key Concepts | Hardware | Status |
|-------|---------|--------------|----------|--------|
| Timing and Frequency | 555-timer LED flasher | Oscillation, frequency control | 555 timer, LEDs, resistors | Materials bought, not Started |
| Analog Sensing | Light-activated relay | Transduction, voltage comparators | LDR, relay, power supply | Materials bought, not Started  |
| Voltage Measurement | Battery indicator circuit | Voltage comparison, LED indication | Multimeter, batteries | Materials bought, not Started  |

**Learning Outcomes:**
- Understand component behavior and timing constants
- Build and test simple circuits on breadboards
- Measure signals with multimeter
- Modify component values and observe direct effects

**Resources:** Breadboards, basic components, multimeter

**Milestones:**
- [ ] 555-timer flasher working by March 2026
- [ ] All three projects completed by March 2026

---

### Phase 2: Digital Control & Microcontrollers (April 2026 ‚Äì June 2026 | Weeks 7‚Äì14)

**Weekly Time Commitment:** 7‚Äì9 hours

| Topic | Project | Key Concepts | Hardware | Status |
|-------|---------|--------------|----------|--------|
| State Machines | Traffic light controller | Sequential logic, PWM | Arduino Uno, LEDs | Not Started |
| Sensor Integration | Temperature monitoring | Analog input, decision logic | Temperature sensor, LCD | Not Started |
| Motor Control | Servo motor positioning | Pulse width modulation (PWM) | Servo, potentiometer | Not Started |
| Multi-sensor Logic | Motion-detection alarm | Sensor fusion, threshold logic | PIR sensor, buzzer | Not Started |

**Learning Outcomes:**
- Write C/C++ sketches for Arduino
- Interface sensors to microcontroller
- Implement real-time control loops
- Debug and observe behavioral changes with code modifications

**Resources:** Arduino Uno, sensors, development environment (Arduino IDE)

**Milestones:**
- [ ] Traffic light controller working by November 2025
- [ ] All four projects completed by December 2025
- [ ] Comfortable with Arduino programming by end of phase

---

### Phase 3: Analog Electronics & Signal Conditioning (July ‚Äì September 2026 | Weeks 15‚Äì22)

**Weekly Time Commitment:** 8‚Äì10 hours | **Parallel to:** Differential calculus completion, Python completion

| Topic | Project | Key Concepts | Hardware | Status |
|-------|---------|--------------|----------|--------|
| Amplification | Non-inverting amplifier | Gain calculation, frequency response | Op-amps (TL072), function generator | Not Started |
| Differential Sensing | Differential amplifier | CMRR, noise rejection | Instrumentation amp (INA128) | Not Started |
| Filtering | Active low-pass filter | Cutoff frequency, roll-off | Op-amp filters, oscilloscope | Not Started |
| Bioamplifier | ECG front-end (3-stage) | Real specifications, noise performance | ECG electrodes, custom circuit | Not Started |

**Learning Outcomes:**
- Design op-amp circuits with specific gain
- Measure frequency response using function generator
- Understand filtering and noise rejection
- Build realistic bioamplifier for biosignal acquisition

**Critical Tools:**
- Oscilloscope (essential for signal observation)
- Function generator (for frequency sweeps)
- Breadboard and components

**Resources:** Op-amp ICs, resistors, capacitors, oscilloscope access

**Milestones:**
- [ ] Non-inverting amplifier tested by August 2026
- [ ] Differential amplifier working by mid-September 2026
- [ ] Complete ECG amplifier by end of September 2026

---

### Phase 4: Microcontroller Integration & Real-Time Processing (October ‚Äì December 2026 | Weeks 23‚Äì32)

**Weekly Time Commitment:** 8‚Äì10 hours | **Parallel to:** Multivariable Calculus, Neuroscience foundation

| Topic | Project | Key Concepts | Hardware | Status |
|-------|---------|--------------|----------|--------|
| Pulse Oximetry | DIY pulse oximeter | Transimpedance amplification, AC/DC separation | LEDs, photodiode, TIA | Not Started |
| Closed-loop Control | PID temperature controller | Kp, Ki, Kd tuning, feedback systems | Temperature sensor, heater, display | Not Started |
| Muscle Signals | EMG signal acquisition | Electrode placement, gesture recognition | Surface electrodes, amplifier | Not Started |
| Wireless Integration | Bluetooth heart-rate monitor | Wireless protocols, power management, wearables | Bluetooth module, battery | Not Started |

**Learning Outcomes:**
- Integrate analog front-ends with Arduino ADC
- Implement real-time filtering on microcontroller
- Understand sampling and quantization
- Design wearable systems with wireless capability

**Resources:** Teensy 3.6 (recommended for DSP performance), Bluetooth modules, biomedical sensors

**Milestones:**
- [ ] Pulse oximeter functional by Oct 2026
- [ ] PID controller tuned by Nov 2026
- [ ] EMG acquisition working by Nov 2026
- [ ] Wireless integration complete by Dec 2026

---

### Phase 5: Signal Processing & Digital Signal Processing (2027 | Weeks 33‚Äì40)

**Weekly Time Commitment:** 6‚Äì8 hours | **Parallel to:** Multivariable Calculus completion, Diff Eq start, Neuroscience courses

| Topic | Project | Key Concepts | Hardware/Software | Status |
|-------|---------|--------------|-------------------|--------|
| Spectral Analysis | Real-time FFT on embedded system | Frequency domain, Nyquist theorem, aliasing | ArduinoFFT, Teensy, oscilloscope | Not Started |
| Digital Filtering | IIR filter implementation | Filter design, computational efficiency, latency | C++ implementation on microcontroller | Not Started |
| Adaptive Filtering | Motion artifact removal | Adaptive algorithms, correlated noise rejection | Python + embedded testing | Not Started |
| Data Logging | Time-series acquisition | High-speed SD card logging, data export | SD module, data analysis tools | Not Started |

**Learning Outcomes:**
- Implement FFT on resource-constrained hardware
- Design and test digital filters
- Understand real-time processing constraints
- Log and analyze multi-channel data

**Resources:** MATLAB/Python (scipy, numpy), Teensy/STM32, oscilloscope

**Milestones:**
- [ ] Real-time FFT working by 2027
- [ ] IIR filter tested by 2027
- [ ] Adaptive filtering working by 2027
- [ ] Data logging system operational by 2027

---

### Phase 6: Biosignal Acquisition & Neuroengineering Foundations (2027 | Weeks 41‚Äì52)

**Weekly Time Commitment:** 10‚Äì12 hours | **Parallel to:** Differential Equations 2√ó2 Systems, Advanced Neuroscience courses

| Topic | Project | Key Concepts | Hardware/Software | Status |
|-------|---------|--------------|-------------------|--------|
| EEG Acquisition | 10-20 electrode system | Brain rhythm recording, electrode placement, impedance | OpenBCI or custom circuit, MNE-Python | Not Started |
| Spectral Analysis | Alpha rhythm detection | Frequency bands (alpha, beta, theta), Fourier analysis | MNE-Python, scipy | Not Started |
| Multi-modal Decoding | EMG + EEG gesture recognition | Feature extraction, classifier training, cross-validation | scikit-learn, TensorFlow | Not Started |
| Brain-Machine Interface | Motor imagery BCI | Event-related desynchronization (ERD), classification | Custom acquisition + ML pipeline | Not Started |
| Health Monitor | Multi-modal integration | ECG + EMG + motion fusion, anomaly detection | Data fusion algorithms, real-time processing | Not Started |

**Learning Outcomes:**
- Record and process real EEG/EMG data
- Extract relevant features from neural signals
- Train machine learning classifiers
- Build proof-of-concept brain-computer interface
- Integrate multiple biosignal modalities

**Critical Tools:**
- EEG headset (OpenBCI, Emotiv, or custom ADC-based system)
- MNE-Python (neuroscience data processing standard)
- Machine learning libraries (scikit-learn or TensorFlow)
- Signal processing expertise from Phase 5

**Resources:**
- *Neuronal Dynamics* ‚Äì Gerstner et al.
- *Theoretical Neuroscience* ‚Äì Dayan & Abbott
- MNE-Python documentation and tutorials
- OpenBCI community resources

**Milestones:**
- [ ] EEG recording system working by 2027
- [ ] Alpha rhythm detected and visualized by 2027
- [ ] EMG + EEG multi-modal classifier trained by 2027
- [ ] Motor imagery BCI functional by 2027
- [ ] Multi-modal health monitor integrated by 2027

