### Phase 7: Advanced Digital Design & System Integration (2027 | Weeks 53‚Äì64)

**Weekly Time Commitment:** 9‚Äì11 hours | **Parallel to:** Linear Algebra, Advanced Neuroscience simulations

| Topic | Project | Key Concepts | Hardware/Software | Status |
|-------|---------|--------------|-------------------|--------|
| PCB Design | Custom bioamplifier PCB | Schematic capture, layout, manufacturing | KiCad, JLCPCB/PCBWay | Not Started |
| High-speed Signal Processing | 64+ channel EEG system | FPGA acceleration, high-speed ADC, data streaming | Vivado/Quartus, Basys 3 FPGA (~$100) | Not Started |
| Real-time OS | FreeRTOS integration | Task scheduling, concurrent sampling/processing | FreeRTOS, STM32 microcontroller | Not Started |
| Power Management | Wearable battery design | Low-power architectures, wireless efficiency | Battery analysis, power profiling | Not Started |
| Signal Integrity | EMI shielding, impedance matching | Noise reduction, grounding strategies, measurement | Oscilloscope, network analyzer | Not Started |

**Learning Outcomes:**
- Design production-quality PCBs
- Implement FPGA-accelerated signal processing
- Manage real-time operating system tasks
- Build low-power, wireless-capable devices
- Ensure signal integrity in biomedical systems

**Resources:**
- KiCad (open-source PCB design)
- Vivado/Quartus (FPGA design suites)
- FreeRTOS (real-time OS)
- Git version control

**Milestones:**
- [ ] PCB designed and ordered by 2027
- [ ] FPGA signal processing working by 2027
- [ ] FreeRTOS multi-task system operational by 2027
- [ ] Power profiling and optimization by 2027

