## Hardware & Software Tools Reference

### Essential Equipment Checklist

**Phase 1‚Äì2 (Basic):**
- [ ] Breadboards, jumper wires, basic components
- [ ] Arduino Uno starter kit
- [ ] Digital multimeter

**Phase 3 (Intermediate):**
- [ ] Oscilloscope (used/low-cost acceptable)
- [ ] Function generator
- [ ] Op-amp ICs, precision resistors/capacitors
- [ ] ~~$200‚Äì400~~

**Phase 4‚Äì5 (Advanced):**
- [ ] Teensy 3.6 or STM32 microcontroller
- [ ] Biomedical sensors (temperature, light, motion)
- [ ] SD card module for data logging

**Phase 6 (Biosignal):**
- [ ] EEG headset (OpenBCI ~$500, Emotiv ~$300, or custom)
- [ ] Surface electrodes for EMG/ECG
- [ ] Conductive gel/paste
- [ ] ~~$300‚Äì800 depending on choice~~

**Phase 7‚Äì8 (Professional):**
- [ ] PCB prototyping (JLCPCB/PCBWay, ~$20‚Äì50 per iteration)
- [ ] Basys 3 FPGA board (~$100)
- [ ] SMD soldering equipment (reflow oven or hot plate)
- [ ] Precision measurement tools (power meter, network analyzer)

**Total Hardware Investment:** ~$1500‚Äì2500 over 18 months

